{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":23808,"name":"","username":"Dave82","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/dave82/{size}/2369_2.png","created_at":"2018-03-22T18:51:17.425Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003ePlaying with particles.The demo uses two emitters 1. Rain is a simple emitter with long particles + big velocity,\u003cbr\u003e\n2 . Splash. The splash is achived by expanding the ParticleEmitter and ParticleEffect with a new emittertype called ‚ÄúEMITTER_MESH‚Äù.It takes a mesh as a shape and generates random points inside it‚Äôs triangles.The direction of the particle is calculated from the triangle‚Äôs normal.Since it uses a very cheap solution it can generate extremely big amount of particles (almost no frame drop).The only drawbacks are : On bigger triangles there will be less particles than on a smaller set of triangles.(ground plane VS sphere cap in the video) however it can be easily solved.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lazyYT\" data-youtube-id=\"zqZzB8YXfq8\" data-youtube-title=\"Urho3d Simple Rain\" data-width=\"480\" data-height=\"270\" data-parameters=\"feature=oembed\u0026amp;wmode=opaque\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-22T18:51:17.425Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":37,"reads":72,"readers_count":71,"score":501.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":4116,"topic_slug":"simple-rain-demo","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zqZzB8YXfq8","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"YouTube","clicks":7},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/anyone-mine-sharing-a-rain-or-snow-particle-xml-file/3841/5","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Anyone mine sharing a rain or snow particle xml file?","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":16}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":247,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":23968,"name":"","username":"coldev","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/c/73ab20/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-03-31T03:58:00.815Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003esource download please   \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/grin.png?v=5\" title=\":grin:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":grin:\"\u003e  thanks\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-31T03:58:00.815Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":61,"readers_count":60,"score":42.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":4116,"topic_slug":"simple-rain-demo","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":588,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":23976,"name":"","username":"Dave82","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/dave82/{size}/2369_2.png","created_at":"2018-03-31T22:46:26.981Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWell the rain itself is pretty easy :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;particleeffect\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;material name=\"Materials/rain.xml\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;numparticles value=\"4000\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;updateinvisible enable=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;relative enable=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;scaled enable=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;animlodbias value=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;emittertype value=\"Sphere\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;emittersize value=\"200 1 200\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;direction min=\"-0.04 -1 -0.04\" max=\"0.04 -1 0.04\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;dampingforce value=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;activetime value=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;inactivetime value=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;emissionrate min=\"2000\" max=\"2500\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;particlesize min=\"0.15 25\" max=\"0.25 35\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;timetolive min=\"0.5\" max=\"0.6\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;velocity min=\"700\" max=\"800\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;constantforce value=\"0 -46 0\" /\u0026gt;\n\t\u0026lt;color value=\"0.08 0.085 0.09 0.1\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/particleeffect\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSet your emitter face camera mode to rotate only bi y (emitter-\u0026gt;SetFaceCameraMode(FC_ROTATE_Y)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMaterial  :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/DiffVColAdd.xml\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"Textures/rain.bmp\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt; \u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRain rexture (rain.bmp):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/5/52402b24557f434cdcd43b6ff2742a9f390c85cf.png\" width=\"8\" height=\"128\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnfortunately the raindrop effect requires massive rework of the existing ParticleEmitter and ParticleEffect classes that in this particular state (which i use) wouldn‚Äôt be accepted PR.(scale frames , random texture frames, etc ) Instead i‚Äôm thinking of adding a general purpose template based interpolator (like in SPARK) which can be used to manipulate the parameters of the particles.Would be more convenient to use and easy to expand in the future .\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso you have to modify the EmitNewParticle() function to\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003ebool EmitNewParticle(const unsigned char* \u0026amp;vertexData, unsigned vertexSize, unsigned vertexCount , const unsigned char* \u0026amp;indexData, unsigned indexSize);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eto avoid mesh vertex buffer lock each time a new particle is emitted.I don‚Äôt know is there any better workaround for this but this is how i use it right now.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-03-31T22:56:43.519Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":111.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4116,"topic_slug":"simple-rain-demo","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":247,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":"downloaded local copies of images","can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[23808,23968,23976]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,1706],[2,1698],[3,1697]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7095,"title":"Texture2D from imported GPU memory (interop)","fancy_title":"Texture2D from imported GPU memory (interop)","slug":"texture2d-from-imported-gpu-memory-interop","posts_count":6,"reply_count":2,"highest_post_number":6,"image_url":null,"created_at":"2021-12-09T10:52:31.426Z","last_posted_at":"2021-12-13T15:40:35.300Z","bumped":true,"bumped_at":"2021-12-13T15:40:35.300Z","archetype":"regular","unseen":false,"pinned":fa